Motorists will see a massive fuel price drop on Wednesday, BusinessTech reported. The price for 93 and 95 petrol will decrease by R1.84 per litre. Diesel will decrease by R1.45 and R1.47, and illuminating paraffin will drop by R1.33. The price cuts will come as a relief for consumers after multiple months of big price hikes in 2018. The new fuel prices are: